.TH VEK_BACKEND_NAME 3 "2024-01-01" "vek 0.8.0" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
vek_backend_name \- get the name of the active SIMD backend
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <vek.h>
.sp
.BI "const char* vek_backend_name(void);"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR vek_backend_name ()
returns the name of the SIMD backend currently in use.
.PP
The backend is selected once at first API call (or explicitly via
.BR vek_init (3))
based on detected CPU features.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns a pointer to one of the following static strings:
.TP
.B "scalar"
Pure C reference implementation (always available).
.TP
.B "sse2"
SSE2 intrinsics (x86_64 baseline).
.TP
.B "avx2"
AVX2 + FMA3 intrinsics.
.TP
.B "avx512"
AVX-512F + VNNI + VPOPCNTDQ intrinsics.
.TP
.B "neon"
ARM64 NEON intrinsics.
.PP
The returned pointer is to a static string and must not be freed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
printf("Using: %s\\n", vek_backend_name());  // e.g. "avx512"
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vek_init (3)
